payload.Description: Path to the payload in the message. Enrich will add only the payload to the enriched message, other fields will not be kept except for in the indexes.

timestamp.Description: Path to an RFC3339 timestamp in the message. If no path is provided, the ingestion time of the record is used for time-based joins.

ttl.Description: Time to live for individual records.

keys.Description: List of keys that can be used for joining on enrich.

path.Description: Path to the input value from the message.

primaryKey.Description: If true the property will be used as a primary key. At most one primary key can exists.
